{
  "texts": [
    "The study by Duru et al (2021) used DL models to predict the performance of different English second language speakers who were categorized according to their likely linguistic abilities.",
    "The dataset used within the proposed model included about 420,000 comments that the University of Southampton delivered through the Future-Learn MOOC.",
    "This study divided language learners into three categories: those for whom English is their official second language (ESL), those for whom English is their official first language but not a primary (EOL), and those for whom English is their official first and Primary Language (EPL).",
    "Different DL models (CNN, GRU, LSTM, Bi-LSTM, and CNN-LSTM) have been proposed to leverage either extracted features from user activities during the course or comment texts alone, or a mix of both.",
    "The results showed that the DL models outperformed when using a combination of both extracted features and comment texts rather than when using comment texts alone."
  ]
}